author: Inside Edition
description: Police say they have identified three teenagers who terrorized a family after appearing at the front door in scary Halloween costumes. No charges will be filed in the story that got national attention.
title: No Charges Filed After 3 Teens Identified In Scary Costume Case #shorts

author: Inside Edition
description: There are new questions about President Donald Trump's health Monday after he revealed that he had an MRI at his hospital check-up earlier this month. The White House has not released the results of the president's tests. His doctor wrote a memo, stating in general terms, that Trump underwent "advanced imaging … to ensure optimal cardiovascular health" and concluded that "President Trump remains in exceptional health."
title: New Questions About President Trump's Health After Recent MRI

author: Inside Edition
description: Twenty-three-year-old Audrey Eckert beat out 50 other contestants to win the new Miss USA crown. However, the crowning ceremony is coming with a big heap of controversy. The reigning Miss USA stunned the pageant world when she refused to attend this year's pageant. Typically the current Miss USA crowns the new Miss USA. The reigning Miss USA, Alma Cooper, wrote on Instagram that she "made the extremely difficult decision not to attend." The new Miss USA was crowned by Miss Universe.
title: Reigning Miss USA Alma Cooper Not Present To Crown New Miss USA

author: Inside Edition
description: Sports commentator Pat McAfee put up $500,000 of his own money as college game day landed at Vanderbilt University. Tyler Wang, an engineering and economics major, won the lottery to make the field goal kick. He did not know he'd be doing it for half a million dollars until seconds before the big moment. Wang made the goal. McAfee called it the most impressive kick of the season. So far this year, McAfee has given away a total of $2.6 million to college day field goal winners.
title: Vanderbilt Student Wins $500K After Impressive Field Goal Kick

author: Inside Edition
description: An American skied down the world's highest peak. Adventurer Jim Morrison is the first person to ski down Everest's most challenging route, a narrow and steep gully on the infamous North Face. Before he could ski down, Morrison first had to make the arduous climb to the top. Morrison appeared on Good Morning America Monday. Also in the studio was the filmmaker Jimmy Chin who shot the unbelievable footage. The adventure is the subject of a new National Geographic special.
title: American Adventurer First Person Ever To Ski Down Mount Everest

author: Inside Edition
description: Cops rushed to the scene as a team of good Samaritans tried to find a baby trapped under an overturned SUV. The mother was thrown from the vehicle and was lying in the grass. The car was going to have to be lifted to save the child. Police and the passersby pitched in to help. Second later, the infant was found but she was not breathing. After chest compressions, the baby was brought back to life and taken to a waiting ambulance.
title: Baby Saved After Being Trapped Under Overturned SUV

author: Inside Edition
description: Police say they have identified three teenagers who terrorized a family after appearing at the front door in scary Halloween costumes. No charges will be filed in the story that got national attention. It turned out that the three culprits are relatives of the family that lived in the house. It seems it was all an elaborate Halloween prank that went horribly wrong. A widow, her adult daughter, and a child were inside the house and told Inside Edition they were truly terrified.
title: No Charges Filed After 3 Teens in Scary Costumes Identified: Cops

author: Inside Edition
description: An arts and crafts influencer was reportedly arrested for possession and distribution of child sexual abuse images. Michael David Booth is known to his followers as Mr. Crafty Pants. His YouTube channel, which is now deactivated, reportedly has 600,000 subscribers, plus thousands more across his other social media platforms. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: Arts And Crafts Influencer Accused Of Possessing And Sharing Child SA Material

author: Inside Edition
description: It started off as a hobby, a way for Dick Baughn to stay active in his retirement, but the game of tennis has turned into a passion. Baughn of Texas has been playing now for 50 years, which amounts to about half of his life since he turned 102 years old recently. He may have started tennis at age 50, but he says he doesn't know where he would be if he hadn't taken a liking to the sport. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: 102-Year-Old Tennis Player Stays Active On The Court

author: Inside Edition
description: A man was dragged from behind the wheel of his luxury car by three robbers brandishing guns. They were determined to steal his #Swisswatch worth more than $600,000.
title: Crooks Drag Man From Car For His Swiss Watch #shorts
